---
import ContactLinks from "~/components/ContactLinks.astro";
import SectionBlock from "~/components/SectionBlock.astro";
import Layout from "~/layouts/Layout.astro";

const titleLetters = [... "Aidan Timson"];
const taglineLetters = [... "Software Developer"];
---

<Layout>
  <header
    class="relative h-screen w-full overflow-hidden bg-linear-to-b from-violet-900 to-gray-950 p-4"
    role="banner"
  >
    <div
      class="relative z-10 flex h-full w-full max-w-screen flex-col items-start justify-end bg-contain bg-center bg-no-repeat p-8 md:p-16"
      style="background-image: url('/logo-wide-nobackground.png')"
    >
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-baseline justify-start text-start">
        <h1 class="me-6 text-8xl leading-none font-bold tracking-tight text-white">
          {
            titleLetters.map((letter, index) => (
              <span
                class="hero-letter inline-block"
                style={`animation-delay: ${index * 0.03}s`}
              >
                {letter === " " ? "\u00A0" : letter}
              </span>
            ))
          }
        </h1>
        <span
          class="hero-reveal text-4xl leading-none font-bold tracking-normal text-nowrap"
          style="animation-delay: 0.45s"
        >
          <span class="text-gray-200">Timmo</span> /{" "}
          <span class="text-gray-200">@timmo001</span>
        </span>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-4 text-3xl leading-snug font-semibold tracking-tight text-wrap text-white">
        {
          taglineLetters.map((letter, index) => (
            <span
              class="hero-letter inline-block"
              style={`animation-delay: ${0.35 + index * 0.015}s`}
            >
              {letter === " " ? "\u00A0" : letter}
            </span>
          ))
        }
      </p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div
    class="flex w-full flex-col items-center justify-start px-4 py-16"
    role="main"
  >
    <div
      class="stagger-grid container grid gap-x-4 gap-y-36 px-2 sm:grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2"
    >
      <h3 class="reveal text-3xl leading-snug font-bold tracking-tight text-white">
        About Me
      </h3>
      <div class="reveal">
        <SectionBlock>
          My name is Aidan, but you might know me better as{" "}
          <a
            class="text-indigo-500 transition-colors hover:text-indigo-400"
            href="https://github.com/timmo001"
            target="_blank"
            aria-label="GitHub profile"
          >
            Timmo
          </a>{" "}
          or{" "}
          <a
            class="text-indigo-500 transition-colors hover:text-indigo-400"
            href="mailto:aidan@timmo.dev"
            target="_blank"
            aria-label="Email"
          >
            @timmo001
          </a>
          .
          <br />
          <br />
          I am a full-stack software developer with a passion for creating and
          maintaining software. I have experience in full-stack development and
          have worked on a variety of projects.
          <br />
          <br />
          I'm a tinkerer, who has a vast interest for technology, automation and
          software. I am always looking to improve my skills and learn new things,
          whether that be a new programming language, framework or technology.
        </SectionBlock>
      </div>

      <h3 class="reveal text-3xl leading-snug font-bold tracking-tight text-white">
        Personal Projects / Open-Source Contributions
      </h3>
      <div class="reveal">
        <SectionBlock>
          I am very passionate about open-source projects and the open-source
          community. Alongside my own personal projects, I have contributed to
          projects such as{" "}
          <a
            class="text-indigo-500"
            href="https://www.home-assistant.io"
            target="_blank"
            aria-label="Home Assistant website"
          >
            Home Assistant
          </a>
          , the{" "}
          <a
            class="text-indigo-500"
            href="https://github.com/hassio-addons"
            target="_blank"
            aria-label="Home Assistant Community Add-ons GitHub repository"
          >
            Home Assistant Community Add-ons
          </a>{" "}
          project and others.
          <br />
          <br />
          For a comprehensive view of my contributions to open-source projects
          and other creations, please visit my website and{" "}
          <a
            class="text-indigo-500"
            href="https://github.com/timmo001"
            target="_blank"
            aria-label="GitHub profile"
          >
            GitHub
          </a>{" "}
          profile.
        </SectionBlock>
      </div>

      <div class="reveal">
        <SectionBlock heading="System Bridge">
          System Bridge is a desktop application for controlling and monitoring
          your desktops. The app is designed to be cross-platform, easy to install
          and use, and directly integrate with Home Assistant or your own
          application via its websocket API. System Bridge started as a node
          application using electron, but moved into a python application and then
          into Rust with a Python backend, using the original Python code moved
          from a monorepo to individual modules.
        </SectionBlock>
      </div>

      <div class="reveal">
        <SectionBlock heading="Other Personal Projects">
          You will also find a lot of smaller projects, which showcase my passion
          for open-source and creating applications. The reason could be 'this
          could be better', or 'can this be a thing' etc. There isn't always a
          reason, it can be because I want to learn a new language or use a
          framework that interests me and the best way to learn a technology in my
          opinion is to use it and experience what it is capable of.
        </SectionBlock>
      </div>

      <h3 class="reveal text-3xl leading-snug font-bold tracking-tight text-white">
        Top Programming Languages
      </h3>
      <p class="reveal mb-8 text-xl leading-relaxed font-normal tracking-normal text-white">
        I have experience in a variety of programming languages. My top programming
        languages can be found on the{" "}
        <a class="text-indigo-500" href="/stats">stats</a> page.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="col-span-full mt-36 flex w-full flex-col items-center gap-8">
      <h3 class="reveal mb-8 text-2xl leading-snug font-bold tracking-tight text-white">
        Contact
      </h3>
      <div class="reveal flex w-full flex-row flex-wrap justify-center gap-x-24 gap-y-16">
        <ContactLinks
          classes="h-32 w-32 fill-white transition-transform duration-300 ease-in-out hover:scale-110"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
